reviewText: Delivery of this product was as expected in regard to condition and time of arrival - no problems, no surprises.  I love this series!  and now - years later- it is helping my nephew find his way through a very confusing time.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Sad. Oh so very sad. I love this show, it is amazing, and when I saw this complete series box set on this website, I was sooo happy! It's so cute! It's a box! Haha. It's colorful, and reallllly nicely packaged (the only reason I gave it 2 stars) but when I put it in my DVD player and realized how much of it wouldn't work (be it episodes or special features) I was so upset. I already had a few of the seasons on DVD, and realized they had some glitches.. I figured they would have redone the discs for this box set, it wouldn't have the same problem, and id have the complete series! So when I had returned it (got a refund, they wont rip you off on that, thankfully)I was so upset. I also hated to see that there were so many customer reviews telling me not to buy this.. why I didnt scroll down and read customer reviews before hand, Ill never know. I also hate to see that this website, as well as others, are still selling it. IT DOESNT WORK. I say take it off store shelves, and take it off websites until they remake the discs to work properly, and rerelease this set. Sucks to.. I loved it.. even made room on my shelf = ( = P.
Title: N/A

reviewText: I recently purchased Will & Grace:  The Complete Series.  Unfortunately, I did not take heed to the customer reviews about it being defective.  Sure enough, first season, disc 1, episode 3 at approximately 14 min 10 sec the disc froze and I could view the rest of the episode any further.  I tried it again several times and the disc froze at the same point.  I did not check out any other discs.  I returned the product and ordered the individual season discs.So far, so good.  I have watched the entire first season with no problems.
summary: Seems to have a manufacturing defect

reviewText: This may actually be the last of the great Sitcoms . In the tradition of Cheers, Frasier, Friends, Seinfeld and the like - no one in Network is investing this much time, talent & money in quality entertainment anymore . I now own all eight seasons of this hilarious gathering of comedic virtue on 33 discs, I truly relish being able to watch Will & Grace anytime I choose and always knowing I have the perfect alternative to watching the desolate wasteland of shows now being offered . Did I mention the Outtakes and themed featurettes ? Plenty of quality entertainment for any rainy night .

reviewText: I read all the negative reviews before ordering so I can't blame anyone but myself for being disappointed in the quality of the product, which is horrible. The show itself deserves 5 stars so it's a shame to have to downgrade the review based totally on the poor quality. I have tried rewinding and replaying, hoping to see missing minutes but have had no luck. With years of negative reviews I don't understand why Amazon,which is a reputable company, doesn't refuse to sell a known defective product.
summary: great show, defective discs from each years episodes
